docs.lead_paragraph: Femont Clubs in Brooklyn. The Republican young men of Brooklyn have organized a club, under the name of the Rocky MOUNTAIN FREMONT CLUB, and have taken rooms in the Franklin Buildings, on the corner of Fulton and Orange-streets. The rooms are to be open every night, and be well supplied with plenty of papers and public documents for the instruction of its membere.

docs.lead_paragraph: The United States mail steamship Illinois, C. S. BOGGS, Esq., U. S. N.. Commander, left Aspinwall at 8:40 on the evening of the 19th, and arrivived at Kingston, Ja., at 9:20 A. M. on the 22d. Left Kington at 4:30 P. M. same day, and arrived at Quarantine at 4:15 o'clock on the morning of the 28th. She brings the California mails of the 5th instant, $2,270,868 in treasure, on freight, and 924 passengers.
